<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="402" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 123.G35/67a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 12, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Department will give the following to the press to-morrow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>In consideration of his several hard years of service in
                                    Honduras, in the Department of State, and at Habana, it was the
                                    intention of the Department to transfer Mr. Hugh S. Gibson, now
                                    Secretary of Legation at Habana, to be Secretary of Legation at
                                    Brussels. But owing to Mr. Gibson’s special familiarity with
                                    American interests in Cuba, the President has directed that he
                                    be retained at Habana.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>